result.execSummary:
The defendant Joshua Raymond Jashinski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Joshua Raymond Jashinski in court.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.
DOC Agent contacted the court to schedule a review hearing. Review Hearing set for 03/06/2015 at 1:30 PM in branch 23.

RECALLED
Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.
 Received & Filed, papers as to sentencing.
AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to 75 DAYS in the House of Correction, consecutive, FORTHWITH, with Huber privileges for work within Wisconsin as approved by HOC, and AODA treatment. Court Waived all NON-Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges. Defendant to pay all Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges during probation period on Count 3, any bail on deposit to apply, failure to pay results in a civil judgment. Defendant advised any violations will result in loss of Huber release privileges.

AS TO COUNT 3
The court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS, consecutive to Count 2 on this case, and Count 3 on 14CF10.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-Serve 20 DAYS in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with Angela M., C.A.M., Douglas F., Quinton J., and Rachel F., without approval of the the court or agent, except for third party contact for purposes of time with the child, as approved by the agent and After adjudication.
-No driving without a valid license.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.
-Pay all Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation, to be paid form bail on deposit, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
-Court WAIVED all NON-mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges.
-DOC agent to contact the court to set review hearing upon release.

*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief. 
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER
*Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.

Filed: 
-Pretrial Sentence Credit
-Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief
-Memorandum of Conditions of Probation

AS TO COUNT 1
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion from the state, the court ordered Count 1 Dismissed, But Read In.
AS TO COUNTS 2 & 3
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Case passed.

Defendant Joshua Raymond Jashinski in court with attorney Jeffrey W Purnell.  Defendant Joshua Raymond Jashinski in custody.  Matthew G Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
AS TO COUNT 2
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion from the state the court ordered Count 2 Amended to Disorderly Conduct, Domestic Abuse, contrary to Wis. Stat. 947.01(1), 968.075(1)(a) a class B Misdemeanor.

Attorney Jeffrey W Purnell in court, defendant Joshua Raymond Jashinski not in court, in custody.  Matthew G Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant NOT produced.
